<topic xml:id="ha-installing-packages"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Installing the &ha; packages</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        The packages for configuring and managing a cluster are included in the &ha; installation
        pattern. This pattern is only available after the &sleha; extension (&slehaa;) is enabled.
        &slehaa; can be enabled during the installation of &sles; (&slsa;), or after &slsa; is
        already installed.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    Use this procedure to install &slehaa; after &slsa; is already installed.
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <title>Requirements</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        &sles; is installed and registered with the &scc;.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        You have an additional registration code for &sleha;.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Perform this procedure on <emphasis>all</emphasis> the machines you intend to use as
    cluster nodes:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Log in as either the &rootuser; user or a user with <command>sudo</command> privileges.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Enable the &ha; extension:
      </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo &suseconnect; -p sle-ha/&productnumber;/x86_64 -r <replaceable>ADDITIONAL_REGCODE</replaceable></command></screen>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Install the &ha; pattern:</para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo zypper install -t pattern ha_sles</command></screen>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
